The paper proposes an oscillatory neural network, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The network is implemented using two-dimensional tantalum disulfide devices, which operate in the charge density wave regime, making it relevant to the sub-categories of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET), electromagnetism (cs.EM), and materials science (cs.MS). The paper also mentions the potential applications of the network in consumer electronics and defense, which could fall under the sub-category of electronic systems and embedded systems (cs.ETL).
